# The error indicates that we have run out of iron ore in our inventory, which means we cannot insert any more into the furnace.
# The last few operations have not yielded any iron plates, and we are now left without the necessary materials to continue production.

# Given that we have exhausted our iron ore supply, we need to gather more iron ore from nearby patches to resume iron plate production.
# Let's move to the nearest iron ore position to gather more iron ore.

# Move to the nearest iron ore position to gather more resources.
iron_ore_position = nearest(Resource.IronOre)
if iron_ore_position:
    move_to(iron_ore_position)  # Move to the iron ore location
    harvest_resource(iron_ore_position, quantity=10)  # Gather more iron ore
else:
    print("No nearby iron ore patches available!")  # Nothing to gather

# After gathering more iron ore, we will check the inventory.
print(f"Inventory changed to {inspect_inventory()} after gathering iron ore.")  # Check inventory after gathering
print(f"Entities on the map: {get_entities()} after gathering resources.")  # Check entities status again.
